Feb 14 2009 	Classy independence	Having searched reviews for many hotels in San Francisco I couldn't really find the right balance of style, location, service and price, until finding the Fairmont Heritage Place by accident on a holiday rental sight.The hotel is very classy, apartments are spacious, well designed and very well equipped, the kitchens have every mod con you could imagine, the decor is subtle, modern but still in keeping with the heritage of the building. We also had a large terrace overlooking the square and the bay. My only criticism would be that the shower was a bit wimpy. Continental breakfast was handy, and the afternoon cheese and wine hour was a restful hour to while away or play pool.The location of the hotel is great, walking distance from most neighborhoods (Russian Hill is great for restaurants and 7 blocks away, downhill on the way back). Check-in and concierge servers couldn't have been more helpful and the hotel car is very handy. Will definitely stay again when we return.	
